This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring May 1st to May 7th, 2011 as National Charter Schools Week. The proclamation highlights the importance of charter schools in providing innovative education and preparing students for the 21st century. It emphasizes the flexibility and ability of charter schools to spark dialogue and improve teaching and learning methods. The Obama Administration has supported charter schools and encouraged states to improve their laws and policies to benefit students. The proclamation also emphasizes the need for accountability and the closure of underperforming charter schools, as well as replicating successful practices from high-performing charter schools. The article concludes by stating that charter schools play a crucial role in educating future American leaders and calls on states and communities to support them.